q003.question: According to the article, how close was the no-confidence vote against Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, and what unusual step was taken to ensure voting could occur?
q003.answer: The no-confidence vote against Prime Minister Manmohan Singh was so crucial that it resulted in a narrow margin of 275-256 votes. To ensure voting could occur, five members of parliament serving prison sentences were freed to cast votes under the watchful eyes of their jailers.
